    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, `vim._extui` border separator does not follow `fillchars.msgsep`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create `minimal.lua`:\n    ```lua\n    require('vim._extui').enable({\n      enable = true, -- Whether to enable or disable the UI.\n    })\n\n    vim.opt.fillchars = {\n      msgsep = ' ',\n    }\n    ```\n2. `nvim --clean -u nvim_test_extui_msgsep.lua +'echo \"a\\nb\"'`\n3. Observe the separator above the extui message buffer, it is a line instead of empty (spaces)\n\n<img width=\"931\" height=\"986\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3fa4323d-9788-4cf5-8d46-51444e2ba98c\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExtui separator should respect `fillchars.msgsep`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1403+gabd0c882b3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty + tmux\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
